24/06/2009
NICOSIA, Cyprus -- Greek Cypriot opposition party Democratic Rally (DISY) and the Republican Turkish Party (CTP) of Turkish Cypriot leader Mehmet Ali Talat agreed on Monday (June 22nd) to join forces in support of ongoing talks to reunify the divided island, media reported Tuesday. 
The deal was struck during a meeting between DISY leader Nicos Anastasiades and CTP leader Ferdi Soyer in the Turkish Cypriot sector of Nicosia. 
Afterwards, Anastasiades said the parties committed to work towards a solution based on UN resolutions. 
He urged both sides to avoid statements that could harm efforts to find a solution. 
(ANA-MPA, Famagusta Gazette - 23/06/09)
